WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.240 --> 00:00:06.400
[military drum roll]

2
00:00:12.880 --> 00:00:15.440
<i>♪ In Sixteen Hundred Seven ♪</i>

3
00:00:15.520 --> 00:00:18.280
<i>♪ We sailed the open sea ♪</i>

4
00:00:18.360 --> 00:00:20.560
<i>♪ For glory, God and gold ♪</i>

5
00:00:20.600 --> 00:00:23.720
<i>♪ And the Virginia Company ♪</i>

6
00:00:23.760 --> 00:00:26.520
<i>♪ For the New World</i>
<i>is like heaven ♪</i>

7
00:00:26.560 --> 00:00:29.360
<i>♪ And we'll all</i>
<i>be rich and free ♪</i>

8
00:00:29.400 --> 00:00:31.560
<i>♪ Or so we have been told ♪</i>

9
00:00:31.600 --> 00:00:34.840
<i>♪ By the Virginia Company ♪</i>

10
00:00:34.920 --> 00:00:37.160
<i>♪ So we have been told ♪</i>

11
00:00:37.240 --> 00:00:40.560
<i>♪ By the Virginia Company ♪</i>

12
00:00:40.680 --> 00:00:42.480
[whistles, chattering]

13
00:00:45.440 --> 00:00:46.920
[baby crying]

14
00:00:50.920 --> 00:00:53.160
<i>♪ For glory, God, and gold ♪</i>

15
00:00:53.280 --> 00:00:56.320
<i>♪ And the Virginia Company ♪</i>

16
00:00:57.360 --> 00:00:59.280
Ready to hoist
the cannon?
Aye!

17
00:00:59.320 --> 00:01:00.800
Hey, look.
Is that Smith?

18
00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:03.240
That's him, all right.
The old sea dog.

19
00:01:03.280 --> 00:01:06.400
Captain John Smith?
I've heard amazing
stories about him.

20
00:01:06.440 --> 00:01:08.520
Are you coming
on this voyage, too?

21
00:01:08.600 --> 00:01:12.640
Course he is, you half-wit!
You can't fight Indians
without John Smith!

22
00:01:12.720 --> 00:01:16.600
That's right. I'm not
about to let you boys
have all the fun.

23
00:01:17.680 --> 00:01:20.240
<i>♪ On the beaches of Virginny ♪</i>

24
00:01:20.280 --> 00:01:22.880
<i>♪ There's diamonds</i>
<i>like debris ♪</i>

25
00:01:22.960 --> 00:01:25.640
<i>♪ There's silver</i>
<i>rivers flowin' ♪</i>

26
00:01:25.720 --> 00:01:28.680
<i>♪ Gold you pick</i>
<i>right off a tree ♪</i>

27
00:01:28.760 --> 00:01:30.760
<i>♪ With a nugget</i>
<i>for my Winnie ♪</i>

28
00:01:30.800 --> 00:01:33.640
<i>♪ And another one for me ♪</i>

29
00:01:33.720 --> 00:01:35.760
<i>♪ And all the rest'll go ♪</i>

30
00:01:35.800 --> 00:01:39.280
<i>♪ To the Virginia Company ♪</i>

31
00:01:39.320 --> 00:01:41.760
<i>♪ It's glory, God, and gold ♪</i>

32
00:01:41.800 --> 00:01:47.320
<i>♪ And the Virginia Company ♪♪</i>

33
00:01:48.600 --> 00:01:51.200
[howling wind, thunderclaps]

34
00:01:51.280 --> 00:01:55.520
[men yell]
Full anchor release!

35
00:01:55.600 --> 00:01:57.280
Come on, lads!
Come on!

36
00:01:57.320 --> 00:01:59.280
[man] Give me a hand,
someone!

37
00:01:59.320 --> 00:02:00.520
[man 2] Watch out!

38
00:02:00.640 --> 00:02:02.960
[men shout]

39
00:02:04.640 --> 00:02:06.840
[man] Faster!
She's taking on more water!

40
00:02:10.680 --> 00:02:12.520
Look out!

41
00:02:16.360 --> 00:02:18.760
John! Get down here!

42
00:02:18.840 --> 00:02:21.280
The cannons
are breaking loose!

43
00:02:25.360 --> 00:02:26.880
Reef the topsails!
Aye, sir!

44
00:02:26.960 --> 00:02:28.720
Steady on your course!

45
00:02:28.800 --> 00:02:31.640
It's all right, Thomas!
We'll get her tied off.

46
00:02:31.680 --> 00:02:32.960
[man] Say your
prayers, lads!

47
00:02:39.320 --> 00:02:41.880
Look out!

48
00:02:42.640 --> 00:02:43.880
Thomas, watch out...!

49
00:02:48.480 --> 00:02:49.840
Help!

50
00:02:50.600 --> 00:02:52.480
[man] Man overboard!

51
00:02:52.560 --> 00:02:53.560
Help!

52
00:02:53.640 --> 00:02:55.720
[man] Stay your course!
He's lost!

53
00:02:55.760 --> 00:02:56.800
Help!

54
00:02:56.880 --> 00:02:59.640
Pull the pin.
[man] Aye, sir!

55
00:03:03.640 --> 00:03:04.760
[man] Smith!

56
00:03:05.880 --> 00:03:07.040
Smith!

57
00:03:08.560 --> 00:03:10.560
Are you crazy?

58
00:03:12.080 --> 00:03:14.640
Hang on, Thomas.
I've got you!

59
00:03:17.040 --> 00:03:19.080
Quick... the rope!

60
00:03:19.920 --> 00:03:21.920
Heave!

61
00:03:26.760 --> 00:03:28.800
Come on, lads! Pull!

62
00:03:31.520 --> 00:03:33.560
Pull! Pull!

63
00:03:33.600 --> 00:03:35.360
Put your back into it!

64
00:03:35.440 --> 00:03:38.480
Pull! Pull!

65
00:03:38.560 --> 00:03:39.680
Hang on!

66
00:03:39.760 --> 00:03:42.520
[grunting, gasping]

67
00:03:42.600 --> 00:03:44.920
Ah, my lucky lad!

68
00:03:45.760 --> 00:03:48.760
Well, that was refreshing.

69
00:03:48.800 --> 00:03:51.880
Well done, Smith.
Of course...

70
00:03:51.920 --> 00:03:53.640
...you'd all do
the same for me.

71
00:03:54.600 --> 00:03:55.800
Yes, yes.
Sure, sure.

72
00:03:55.920 --> 00:03:58.400
Of course we would!
Absolutely!
Yeah, we would.

73
00:04:00.440 --> 00:04:02.360
Trouble on deck?

74
00:04:02.440 --> 00:04:03.760
Governor Ratcliffe!

75
00:04:03.800 --> 00:04:05.360
Thomas fell
overboard, sir.

76
00:04:05.440 --> 00:04:07.680
Thank heavens he's been
successfully retrieved.

77
00:04:07.760 --> 00:04:09.920
Well done, Smith.
Thank you, sir.

78
00:04:09.960 --> 00:04:14.360
Don't lose heart, men.
It won't be long before
we reach the New World,

79
00:04:14.480 --> 00:04:17.800
and remember what
awaits us there...

80
00:04:17.840 --> 00:04:19.360
Freedom...
[barking]

81
00:04:19.440 --> 00:04:20.880
...prosperity...
[barking]

82
00:04:20.960 --> 00:04:22.960
...the adventure
of our lives.

83
00:04:23.040 --> 00:04:25.640
You're the finest crew
England has to offer,

84
00:04:25.720 --> 00:04:27.960
and nothing,
not wind nor rain,

85
00:04:28.080 --> 00:04:31.800
nor a thousand
bloodthirsty savages
shall stand in our way.

86
00:04:31.840 --> 00:04:34.160
Carry on, men!
[cheering]

87
00:04:35.640 --> 00:04:37.640
A stirring oration, sir.

88
00:04:37.680 --> 00:04:40.560
I'm sure the men
were most exhilarated!

89
00:04:40.640 --> 00:04:41.960
Let us hope so.

90
00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:46.560
I'll need those
witless peasants to
dig up my gold, won't I?

91
00:04:46.640 --> 00:04:47.680
[growling]

92
00:04:47.720 --> 00:04:51.080
This New World's
going to be great, John.

93
00:04:51.160 --> 00:04:53.000
I'm going to get
a pile of gold,

94
00:04:53.040 --> 00:04:57.680
build me a big house,
and if any Indian tries
to stop me, I'll blast him.

95
00:04:57.720 --> 00:05:00.400
Just worry about that
fortune of yours, Thomas.

96
00:05:00.480 --> 00:05:01.720
Leave the savages to me.

97
00:05:01.800 --> 00:05:03.520
You think they'll
give us trouble?

98
00:05:03.600 --> 00:05:06.640
Not as much trouble
as Smith'll give them.

99
00:05:06.680 --> 00:05:08.960
[men laugh]
<i>♪ We'll kill</i>
<i>ourselves an injun ♪</i>

100
00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:11.840
<i>♪ Or maybe two or three ♪</i>

101
00:05:11.880 --> 00:05:17.040
<i>♪ We're stalwart men and bold</i>
<i>of the Virginia Company ♪♪</i>

102
00:05:17.080 --> 00:05:19.720
What do you suppose
the New World will
look like?

103
00:05:19.840 --> 00:05:21.680
Like all the others,
I suppose.

104
00:05:21.760 --> 00:05:24.880
I've seen hundreds
of New Worlds, Thomas.

105
00:05:24.960 --> 00:05:27.680
What could possibly be
different about this one?

106
00:05:27.800 --> 00:05:29.920
<i>♪ It's glory, God, and gold ♪</i>

107
00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:33.880
<i>♪ And the Virginia Company ♪♪</i>

108
00:05:36.080 --> 00:05:38.880
<i>[tribal drumming]</i>

109
00:05:52.560 --> 00:05:54.520
<i>♪ Hega hega ♪</i>

110
00:05:54.560 --> 00:05:56.760
<i>♪ Ya-hi-ye hega ♪</i>

111
00:05:56.840 --> 00:05:59.080
<i>♪ Ya-hi-ye-ne-he ♪</i>

112
00:05:59.120 --> 00:06:00.640
<i>♪ Hega ♪</i>

113
00:06:00.720 --> 00:06:04.000
[horn blowing]

114
00:06:04.080 --> 00:06:06.440
<i>♪ Hega, hega ♪</i>

115
00:06:06.520 --> 00:06:08.880
<i>♪ Ya-hi-ye hega ♪</i>

116
00:06:08.920 --> 00:06:11.080
<i>♪ Ya-hi-ye-ne-he ♪</i>

117
00:06:11.160 --> 00:06:12.760
<i>♪ Hega ♪</i>

118
00:06:15.920 --> 00:06:18.160
<i>♪ Steady as the beating drum ♪</i>

119
00:06:18.240 --> 00:06:20.760
<i>♪ Singing to the cedar flute ♪</i>

120
00:06:20.840 --> 00:06:22.960
<i>♪ Seasons go</i>
<i>and seasons come ♪</i>

121
00:06:23.040 --> 00:06:27.440
<i>♪ Bring the corn</i>
<i>and bear the fruit ♪</i>

122
00:06:27.520 --> 00:06:29.520
<i>♪ By the waters</i>
<i>sweet and clean ♪</i>

123
00:06:29.600 --> 00:06:31.840
<i>♪ Where the mighty</i>
<i>sturgeon lives ♪</i>

124
00:06:31.920 --> 00:06:34.440
<i>♪ Plant the squash</i>
<i>and reap the bean ♪</i>

125
00:06:34.520 --> 00:06:38.520
<i>♪ All the earth</i>
<i>our Mother gives ♪</i>

126
00:06:38.600 --> 00:06:40.840
<i>♪ O, Great Spirit,</i>
<i>hear our song ♪</i>

127
00:06:40.960 --> 00:06:43.120
<i>♪ Help us keep</i>
<i>the ancient ways ♪</i>

128
00:06:43.160 --> 00:06:46.040
<i>♪ Keep the sacred fires</i>
<i>strong ♪</i>

129
00:06:46.120 --> 00:06:49.760
<i>♪ Walk in balance</i>
<i>all our days ♪</i>

130
00:06:49.800 --> 00:06:51.960
<i>♪ Seasons go</i>
<i>and seasons come ♪</i>

131
00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:54.560
<i>♪ Steady as</i>
<i>the beating drum ♪</i>

132
00:06:54.640 --> 00:06:58.680
<i>♪ Plum to seed</i>
<i>to bud to plum ♪</i>

133
00:06:58.760 --> 00:07:01.120
[whooping]

134
00:07:01.200 --> 00:07:05.760
<i>♪ Steady as</i>
<i>the beating drum ♪</i>

135
00:07:05.800 --> 00:07:08.240
<i>♪ Ya-hi-ye hega ♪</i>

136
00:07:08.320 --> 00:07:10.960
<i>♪ Ya-hi-ye-ne-he hega ♪♪</i>

137
00:07:11.000 --> 00:07:13.120
Hey! Oof!

138
00:07:15.840 --> 00:07:19.840
[speaking Algonquian]

139
00:07:19.920 --> 00:07:22.120
It's good to be home.

140
00:07:22.160 --> 00:07:24.240
[speaking Algonquian]

141
00:07:24.320 --> 00:07:26.680
The Massawomecks
are defeated!

142
00:07:26.800 --> 00:07:28.680
With the help
of our brothers,

143
00:07:28.800 --> 00:07:31.160
our villages
are safe again.

144
00:07:31.240 --> 00:07:33.000
[cheering]

145
00:07:33.080 --> 00:07:37.000
Your return has brought
much joy to the village.

146
00:07:37.040 --> 00:07:40.080
Look at all
the smiling faces.
[giggling]

147
00:07:40.160 --> 00:07:44.040
Yes. But there's one
smiling face I don't see.

148
00:07:44.120 --> 00:07:45.280
Where is my daughter?

149
00:07:45.360 --> 00:07:47.160
You know Pocahontas.

150
00:07:47.240 --> 00:07:49.200
She has her
mother's spirit.

151
00:07:49.280 --> 00:07:52.360
She goes wherever
the wind takes her.

152
00:07:53.200 --> 00:07:55.920
[leaves rustling]

153
00:08:10.840 --> 00:08:12.640
[girl] Pocahontas!

154
00:08:13.880 --> 00:08:15.600
Your father's back.

155
00:08:15.720 --> 00:08:17.200
Come down here!

156
00:08:18.040 --> 00:08:19.240
He's back, Flit.

157
00:08:20.240 --> 00:08:23.320
[purring]
[buzzing]

158
00:08:23.360 --> 00:08:25.200
Come on, Meeko!

159
00:08:32.880 --> 00:08:35.400
No! Not that... way.

160
00:08:44.240 --> 00:08:46.600
Show-off.

161
00:08:46.680 --> 00:08:48.720
[clicking tongue]
[trilling]

162
00:08:48.800 --> 00:08:51.280
[purring]

163
00:08:51.360 --> 00:08:53.760
[squeaking]

164
00:08:55.800 --> 00:08:58.080
[whining]
[squeaking]

165
00:09:00.240 --> 00:09:02.000
[shrieking]
Pocahontas?

166
00:09:02.920 --> 00:09:06.760
Pocahontas?
Are you all right?

167
00:09:06.800 --> 00:09:10.720
You'd better be all right,
because I'm not coming in
after you...

168
00:09:10.760 --> 00:09:13.920
[gasping, coughing]

169
00:09:13.960 --> 00:09:17.960
Don't you think we're getting
a little old for these games?

170
00:09:18.040 --> 00:09:21.360
[laughing, shrieking]

171
00:09:21.440 --> 00:09:23.360
[giggling]

172
00:09:24.720 --> 00:09:25.800
[grunting]

173
00:09:25.880 --> 00:09:28.280
[squeaking]

174
00:09:33.400 --> 00:09:34.840
[squeaking]

175
00:09:37.400 --> 00:09:39.600
Help me turn
this thing over.

176
00:09:39.680 --> 00:09:40.720
[chirping]

177
00:09:42.120 --> 00:09:44.120
What were you
doing up there?

178
00:09:44.160 --> 00:09:47.120
Thinking. Meeko!

179
00:09:47.200 --> 00:09:50.240
About the dream again?
Have you figured it out yet?

180
00:09:50.280 --> 00:09:53.120
I know it means something,
I just don't know what.

181
00:09:53.160 --> 00:09:55.200
You should ask
your father about it.

182
00:09:55.320 --> 00:09:56.960
Maybe I should.
[purring]

183
00:09:57.040 --> 00:09:59.240
Come on, Flit.

184
00:09:59.320 --> 00:10:01.960
Quit playing around.
We have to get back.

185
00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:04.640
[deflating sound]

186
00:10:04.680 --> 00:10:07.680
[pounding drum]
[man] ...faced
a determined enemy.

187
00:10:07.760 --> 00:10:10.640
The battle lasted from
the rising of the sun

188
00:10:10.680 --> 00:10:13.000
until the evening
shadows fell.

189
00:10:13.040 --> 00:10:15.320
Our warriors
fought with courage,

190
00:10:15.400 --> 00:10:18.000
but none as bravely
as Kocoum,

191
00:10:18.040 --> 00:10:21.000
for he attacked with
the fierce strength
of the bear.

192
00:10:21.040 --> 00:10:24.280
He has proven
himself to be...
Oh, he is so handsome!

193
00:10:25.160 --> 00:10:26.840
I especially
love the smile.

194
00:10:26.920 --> 00:10:28.880
[man continues]
...destroying every
enemy in his path.

195
00:10:28.960 --> 00:10:31.680
Tonight, we will
feast in his honor.

196
00:10:31.760 --> 00:10:33.360
[cheering, whooping]

197
00:10:35.880 --> 00:10:37.920
My daughter.
<i>Winggapo,</i> Father.

198
00:10:38.000 --> 00:10:40.680
Seeing you
gives me great joy.

199
00:10:40.760 --> 00:10:43.360
I'm so glad
you've come home safely.

200
00:10:43.400 --> 00:10:46.440
Come with me.
We have much
to talk about.

201
00:10:46.520 --> 00:10:49.200
I want to hear everything
you've been doing.

202
00:10:49.280 --> 00:10:51.960
[purring, buzzing]

203
00:10:54.080 --> 00:10:55.400
Father,
for many nights now,

204
00:10:55.480 --> 00:10:57.880
I've been having
a very strange dream.

205
00:10:57.920 --> 00:11:00.200
It's telling me
something's
about to happen,

206
00:11:00.240 --> 00:11:01.400
something exciting.

207
00:11:01.480 --> 00:11:05.320
Yes. Something exciting
is about to happen.

208
00:11:05.360 --> 00:11:07.240
[purring]
Really? What is it?

209
00:11:07.320 --> 00:11:11.040
Kocoum has asked to seek
your hand in marriage.

210
00:11:11.080 --> 00:11:12.480
Marry Kocoum?

211
00:11:12.560 --> 00:11:15.240
[chirping]
[gagging]

212
00:11:15.360 --> 00:11:18.000
I told him it would
make my heart soar.

213
00:11:21.080 --> 00:11:25.040
But he's so... serious.

214
00:11:25.120 --> 00:11:28.200
My daughter, Kocoum
will make a fine husband.

215
00:11:28.240 --> 00:11:32.760
He is loyal and strong and
will build you a good house
with sturdy walls.

216
00:11:32.880 --> 00:11:34.800
With him, you will be
safe from harm.

217
00:11:34.880 --> 00:11:37.760
Father, I think my dream
is pointing me down
another path.

218
00:11:37.880 --> 00:11:39.360
This is the right
path for you.

219
00:11:39.400 --> 00:11:40.840
But why can't I choose...

220
00:11:40.920 --> 00:11:42.400
[gasping]
[growling]

221
00:11:42.440 --> 00:11:44.760
[cuckoo sound]

222
00:11:44.840 --> 00:11:46.920
[growling]
[laughing]

223
00:11:49.400 --> 00:11:52.240
Pocahontas,
come with me.

224
00:11:52.320 --> 00:11:54.120
You are the daughter
of the chief.

225
00:11:54.200 --> 00:11:56.800
It is time to take
your place among
our people.

226
00:11:56.880 --> 00:12:01.440
Even the wild mountain
stream must someday
join the big river.

227
00:12:01.480 --> 00:12:06.000
<i>♪ As the river</i>
<i>cuts his path ♪</i>

228
00:12:06.080 --> 00:12:10.520
<i>♪ Though the river's</i>
<i>proud and strong ♪</i>

229
00:12:10.600 --> 00:12:14.200
<i>♪ He will choose</i>
<i>the smoothest course ♪</i>

230
00:12:15.480 --> 00:12:19.000
That's why rivers
live so long.

231
00:12:19.080 --> 00:12:21.760
<i>♪ They're steady ♪</i>

232
00:12:21.840 --> 00:12:26.000
<i>♪ As the steady</i>
<i>beating drum ♪♪</i>

233
00:12:26.080 --> 00:12:29.120
Your mother wore this
for our wedding.

234
00:12:29.200 --> 00:12:32.480
It was her dream to see
you wear it at your own.

235
00:12:34.880 --> 00:12:36.880
It suits you.

236
00:12:36.960 --> 00:12:38.840
[purring]

237
00:12:40.960 --> 00:12:42.960
He wants me
to be steady.

238
00:12:44.080 --> 00:12:45.480
Like the river.

239
00:12:46.520 --> 00:12:48.920
[shrieking, squeaking]

240
00:12:48.960 --> 00:12:51.240
[chuckling]
But it's not steady at all.

241
00:12:51.320 --> 00:12:54.000
[squeaking]

242
00:12:54.080 --> 00:12:56.400
<i>♪ What I love most</i>
